---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="PlantsImpact | About">
  <section
    class="space-y-4 rounded-lg bg-white p-5 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-slate-200"
  >
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">
      FHNW – UCDRE (User-centred Design and Requirements Engineering)
    </h1>
    <p class="text-slate-700">Group 3</p>
    <p class="text-slate-700">
      Avi, Kirishanth, Rayan, Patrick
    </p>
    <p class="text-slate-700">
      PlantsImpact is a semester project developed as part of the User-centred
      Design block of the UCDRE module at FHNW.
    </p>
    <p class="text-slate-700">
      Many people living in cities are not aware of how their daily decisions
      influence the climate. Trees, plants, or even flowers at home can reduce
      CO₂, improve air quality, and contribute to local cooling. However, these
      positive effects are often invisible and underestimated. As a result,
      important climate protection potential remains unused, making it harder to
      develop sustainable and climate-resilient cities.
    </p>
    <p class="text-slate-700">
      PlantsImpact is a prototype and still in progress. It shows demo estimates
      over 1, 2, 5, and 10 years.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
      Disclaimer: all coefficients and sleep-related values are simplified demo
      estimates only, not scientific or medical statements.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
